                     <note xml:lang="shn"/>
                     <note>Story about the illiterate. There was a poor Bodhisatta called Dukkha Sīlavā. Although he was poor he was a moral person, never stole others' properties. He sold flowers for living. One day he had to assist a rich couple to do their farming. The couple had four beautiful daughter. As Dukkha Sīlavā was a good man, the rich couple wanted him to marry with their daughters. But as Dukkha Sīlavā was illiterate, he was sent to study first and then married on his return.</note>
                     <note xml:lang="shn"/>
                     <note>Subject:  commentary,sermon </note>
